# Paths skipped by the Accessibility Checker job in .github/workflows/ci.yml.
# One path per line, relative to the repo root. Keep this list as short as
# possible and record every entry in AGENT_LOG.md with its open issue.
#
# Do not add a page here just to turn the build green. This file is only for
# generated bundles whose markup cannot be corrected in this repository.

# Vite single-file build. The DOM is produced at runtime by the inlined module,
# so the markup cannot be edited here; fixes belong in the upstream source
# project. Known open WCAG AA issue as of 2026-07-22:
#   color-contrast: "0 participants loaded" renders #939eb4 on #273d68 = 3.98:1
#   at 10px, below the 4.5:1 minimum. Suggested source fix: #a4b0c8 (4.93:1).
# Advisory-only findings on this page (not gated, listed for completeness):
#   landmark-one-main, page-has-heading-one, region.
dashboard.html

# Two Google Drive video embeds. The page's own markup was checked and is
# clean; both iframes carry title, allow, loading, and allowfullscreen. The
# only finding is aria-prohibited-attr (x2) inside Google's player markup
# (.ndfHFb-c4YZDc-zTETae), which is rendered by the vendor and cannot be
# corrected here. axe --exclude does not suppress frame-nested findings; see
# the note in .github/workflows/ci.yml.
# Re-check this page by hand if its own markup changes.
media/index.html
